        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 6:20PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 620 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles east of Downtown Asheville, or near Black Mountain, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Black Mountain, Swannanoa, Old Fort, and Montreat.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
